    <div class="gk-tip">
      <strong>What is the 8th Schedule?</strong> Article 344(1) and Article 351 of the Constitution refer to the Eighth Schedule, which lists languages that may be used for official purposes. The Official Languages Commission is set up to recommend progressive use of these languages. Currently <strong>22 languages</strong> are listed.
    </div>

