    <div class="gk-note">
      <strong>Key distinction for Prelims:</strong> Hindi is the <em>Official Language</em> of the Union (Article 343) — NOT the "national language". India has no constitutionally designated "national language". The two official languages of the Union are Hindi and English (for transitional purposes, extended indefinitely). Individual states may have their own official languages under Article 345.
